&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full-Time (1.0 wte) Family and Systemic Psychotherapist - Sussex Family Eating Disorder Service - Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for an experienced Family and Systemic Psychotherapist to join our Specialist Sussex Wide Eating Disorder Service (S-FEDS). You will have the opportunity both for direct clinical work, MDT meetings, systemic case consultations as well as supervising band 7 eating disorder therapists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your locality will be West Sussex where you will be responsible for the timely allocation of young people who have been assessed as requiring NICE Concordant evidence based treatment for eating disorders. We are a lively multidisciplinary team with a supportive systemic supervision structure and ample opportunity to further develop your systemic skills and in particular to become skilled in manualised approaches to treatment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you want a career in a trust with a 2020 vision of achieving outstanding care and treatment you can be confident in? With a vision that includes becoming the employer of choice? Where our values guide how we do this?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As one of the largest providers of children and young people&#39;s mental health, our Care Delivery Service (CDS) provides care across Sussex and Hampshire. Supported by our Clinical Academic Group (CAG) we work to put research, innovation and learning into practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is considered suitable for a job share.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
